==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: amyloid
<hw>am"y*loid</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*loid)</pr>,

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: amyloid
<hw>am"y*loid</hw> <pr>(⟦acr⟧m"⟦icr⟧*loid)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>A starchlike substance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>Any of a group of diverse
starchlike glycoproteins deposited in the organs under some pathological
conditions, such as amyloidosis; they are composed of linear
nonbranching fibrils when viewed under the electron microscope.</def>
<au>Stedman 25</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Amyloid degeneration</b></col> <fld>(Med.)</fld>,
<cd>Same as <er>amyloidosis</er>; -- called also <altname>waxy
degeneration</altname> <it>or</it> <altname>lardaceous
degeneration</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> + <source>AS</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 52 --></p>

<p><ent>amyloidosis</ent>⟦br⟧
